cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the computational complexity of game-theoretic solution concepts, specifically the evolutionarily stable strategy. This makes cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves proving the complexity of a decision problem, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. The use of computational methods and algorithms in game theory also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories.
